title: Address Unknown by Kathrine Kressmann Taylor (.epub)
description:
Address Unknown by Kathrine Kressmann Taylor

Requirements: .ePUB Reader

Overview: Address Unknown is the novel published just before the outbreak of World War 2, written as a series of letters between a Jewish art dealer living in San Francisco and his business partner who had returned to Germany in 1932. It is credited with exposing, early on, the dangers of Nazism to the American public.

Genre: Fiction > General Fiction/Classics
